description: He's the best there is at what he does -and Wolverine's not so bad, either. Writer Jason Aaron's (PUNISHERMAX, Scalped) acclaimed and character-defining Wolverine run continues in this third volume! Joined by some of comics' top artists, Aaron tests Wolverine to his limits as the feral hero takes a lengthy trip through time with the ever-annoying Spider-Man! Then, a mysterious organization conspires to send Wolverine to Hell, where he encounters the souls of unexpected family and friends - and battles the Devil! And the X-Men must help Wolverine regain control of his body from a horde of possessing demons! Plus: Wolverine's girlfriend throws him a birthday party, but where is he? Guest-starring Mystique, Daimon Hellstrom, two Ghost Riders and a host of Marvel heroes! Collecting ASTONISHING SPIDER-MAN & WOLVERINE #1-6, WOLVERINE (2010) #1-9 and #5.1, and material from WOLVERINE: ROAD TO HELL #1.
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: Wolverine by Jason Aaron: The Complete Collection

description: See, you talk to us and we listen. What could be easier? And so it is that, by popular demand, we're making available the whole run of Black Cat Mystery in a run of sumptuous soft covers, each volume containing five to six comic books but without the support material featured in the hardbacks.
name: Volume Three

description: Christmas is right around the corner, and everyone in Riverdale is scrambling to get each other the perfect present! That's a lot easier said than done, especially with Archie and friends! It's the thought that counts, but when Archie gets a really ugly sweater from Veronica, how will he be able to get rid of it without upsetting her? How many times will Betty have to return her Christmas gifts for the gang before she gets it just right? And when Jughead finds out what Archie's getting for the gang, will they jump with joy, or jump him after school?! There are 100 pages of holiday hijinks to enjoy here as you wrap presents for your friends and family. Open your perfect Christmas gift by hitting that Download button now!

When a cabal of military, business and political men attempt to evict the Harperlys and the Mad Mummy, Adam Ray, from his current LA residence he goes on the offensive. It's not nice to mess with a Mad Mummy!

Featuring the World's Best Fantasy, Horror, Sci-Fi and Illustration Artists.

This is the culmination of Infected by Art's first-ever competition held at the beginning of 2013. $10,000 in prize money was awarded to many well deserving artists. Creators from around the globe submitted their best sci-fi/fantasy/horror/illustrated artworks and fans voted online for their favorites. At the end of the competition, the jury panel consisting of Basil Gogos, Ken Kelly, Sanjulian, and Arthur Suydam, selected the best pieces to be included in this massive collection.

This volume contains over 300 pages of art, with over 80% of the images filling the full page to best display the artwork! It’s a who’s who of today’s top artists. To begin, each of the jury members is featured in three pages of art and biography.

This is broken down into five art categories. Just more than half the book is the general category which I would call Fantastic Art, with Grand Prize winners including Igor Kieryluk (Poland), Filip Burburan (Croatia), Ciruelo (Spain), Philippe Fernandez (U.S.), and Steven Stahlberg (U.S) one of our favorite Spectrum artists.

Next is Horror, with awards going to Jyri Straechav (Finland), Peter Morhbacher, Stahlberg again.

The Sci-Fi section winners are Ken Barthelmey (Luxembourg), Gary Freeman (U.S.), Oliver Wetter (Germany).

The Illustration category winners are Daren Horley (U.K), Darek Zabrocki (Poland), Huy Thien Nguyen (Vietnam), who we’ve frequently seen before in international collections.

And finally, Unpublished Art, with winners Peter Mohrbacher again, Trevor Smith (U.S), Milivoj Ceran (Croatia).
